			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Disch wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">The big question I have for the APU pages.... how married are you to guys to the idea of illustrating everything in APU cycles (or 'half' cycles, as frequently they have a &quot;.5&quot; tacked on the end) instead of CPU cycles?  I get the logic of why you'd want to use APU cycles, but IMO it makes it super confusing.</div><br />My opinion? NEVER. I don't see a strong reason for counting in APU cycles. Just leave in CPU cycles for my best, <em><span style="text-decoration: underline">please</span></em>.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

